Lisp Development Tools (lisp-dev-tools).

Linux shell scripts for automatization of downloading, compilation and configuring lisp development tools (emacs, slime, sbcl and other lisps ...)

Now supported: Linux Ubuntu 11.04/x86-64.
Providing 10(!) open source lisps:

SBCL - Steel Bank Common Lisp	(http://www.sbcl.org/)
CMUCL - CMU Common Lisp  	(http://www.cons.org/cmucl/)
XCL 	    	   		(http://armedbear.org/)
ECL - Embedded Common Lisp 	(http://ecls.sourceforge.net/)
CLISP        	      		(http://www.clisp.org/)
MKCL - ManKai Common Lisp 	(http://common-lisp.net/project/mkcl/)
ABCL - Armed Bear Common Lisp 	(http://common-lisp.net/project/armedbear/)
WCL    	     	  	 	(http://pgc.com/commonlisp/)
GCL - GNU Common Lisp 	     	(http://www.gnu.org/s/gcl/)
CCL - Clozure Common Lisp	(http://ccl.clozure.com/)

Notes: 
1) CMUCL building only for x86 architecture (required supported x86 on x86-64 architectures).
For succesful building in Ubuntu 11.04 required libc6-dev-i386 package (for installing
run command: "sudo apt-get -y install libc6-dev-i386", instead apt-get preferable used aptitude)

2) GCL building only in CLTL1 compliated mode (probable bug in GCL)

Using:
1) Go to the directory:

$ cd <path-to>/lisp-dev-tools

2) Downloading (by default SBCL), configuring, building, and install into lisp-dev-tools (for portability):

$ ./provide-lisp

3) Running (by default SBCL:

$ ./run-lisp 

4) Providing and running other lisp (example CCL):

$ LISP=ccl ./provide-lisp && LISP=ccl ./run-lisp

5) Get current lisp:

$ ./get-lisp
sbcl

6) Change current lisp:

$ ./change-lisp ccl
Current lisp: ccl

7) Get current lisp version: 

$ ./get-version
1.0.52

8) Change current lisp version (attention: url includes a new version must be valid):

$ ./change-version
Current lisp version: 1.0.52






